Cable Says U.K. Must Not Lose Credibility With Markets

-- B y   A n d r e w   A t k i n s o n
-- 
2011-09-20T16:20:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/cable-says-u-k-must-not-lose-credibility-with-markets.html
Business Secretary Vince Cable said
Britain will stick to its deficit-cutting program, saying the
country must not lose its credibility with financial markets.  Speaking in an interview with BBC Radio 4, Cable said the
International Monetary Fund’s downwardly revised forecasts for
the economy were “broadly plausible.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
